<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1436,719,1231]" pageId="8" pageNumber="56">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,228,719,745]" pageId="8" pageNumber="56">Notes.</emphasis>
During the present study, through the courtesy of A. Matov (ZISP), we examined the 
<typeStatus box="[1240,1342,720,746]" pageId="8" pageNumber="56">holotype</typeStatus>
and the genitalic preparation of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kozhanchikov" authorityYear="1950" box="[434,694,757,782]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Acronicta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="56" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cinerascens">
<emphasis box="[434,694,757,782]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="56">Acronicta cinerascens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
preserved in the collection of ZISP (
<figureCitation box="[1132,1276,757,783]" captionStart="FIGURES 31–32" captionStartId="14.[151,269,1342,1366]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,199,1308]" captionTargetId="figure-247@14.[151,1436,194,1320]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURES 31–32. 31. Acronicta cinerea (holotype of A. cinerascens, ZISP), adult, North China; 32. A. cinerea (holotype of A. cinerascens, ZISP), male genitalia, prep. 0266 AM; 33, 34, Distribution maps. 31. Acronicta alni and A. naxi; 32. Craniophora pacifica, C. draudti, C. tapaishana and C. simillima." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5302366" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5302366/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="56">Figs. 31, 32</figureCitation>
). The species was described by Kozhanchikov (1950) on the basis of a single specimen from North 
<collectingCountry box="[1167,1241,794,820]" name="China" pageId="8" pageNumber="56">China</collectingCountry>
. The 
<typeStatus box="[1306,1409,794,820]" pageId="8" pageNumber="56">holotype</typeStatus>
is supplemented by labels: “North 
<collectingCountry box="[534,604,832,858]" name="China" pageId="8" pageNumber="56">China</collectingCountry>
Beitsegou Putjata 4-viii-[18]91” (in Russian), “ 
<taxonomicName authority="Han &amp; Kononenko, 2010" authorityName="Han &amp; Kononenko" authorityYear="2010" box="[1174,1436,832,857]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Acronicta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="56" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cinerascens" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis box="[1174,1436,832,857]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="56">Acronicta cinerascens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[151,220,869,895]" pageId="8" pageNumber="56" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
Kozh” and a golden circular label, denoting the 
<typeStatus box="[853,968,869,895]" pageId="8" pageNumber="56">holotype</typeStatus>
. The specimen was not dissected by Kozhanchikov during description. The genitalic preparation was made by A. Matov by our request. After examination of the photographs of the 
<typeStatus box="[613,716,944,970]" pageId="8" pageNumber="56">holotype</typeStatus>
and genitalic slide we concluded that 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Han &amp; Kononenko" authorityYear="2010" box="[1173,1436,944,969]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Acronicta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="56" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cinerascens">
<emphasis box="[1173,1436,944,969]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="56">Acronicta cinerascens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was conspecific with 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hufnagel" authorityYear="1766" box="[414,538,981,1006]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Phalaena" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="56" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cinerea">
<emphasis box="[414,538,981,1006]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="56">A. cinerea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Hufnagel" baseAuthorityYear="1766" box="[555,771,981,1006]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Acronicta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="56" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cinerea">
<emphasis box="[555,771,981,1006]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="56">Acronicta cinerea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is reported for 
<collectingCountry box="[962,1034,981,1007]" name="China" pageId="8" pageNumber="56">China</collectingCountry>
for the first time, while its sister species 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Davis &amp; Schiffermuller" authorityYear="1775" box="[247,419,1018,1043]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Acronicta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="56" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="euphorbiae">
<emphasis box="[247,419,1018,1043]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="56">A. euphorbiae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was reported for 
<collectingCountry box="[638,710,1018,1044]" name="China" pageId="8" pageNumber="56">China</collectingCountry>
by 
<bibRefCitation author="Draudt, M." box="[757,931,1018,1044]" pageId="8" pageNumber="56" refId="ref10251" refString="Draudt, M. (1931) In Seitz (ed). Die Gross-Schmetterlinge der Erde. Volume 3. Supplement. Alfred Kerner. 333 pp., 26 pl." type="book" year="1931">Draudt (1931)</bibRefCitation>
who described subspecies 
<taxonomicName authority="(Draudt, 1931)" baseAuthorityName="Draudt" baseAuthorityYear="1931" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Acronicta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="56" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="euphorbiae" subSpecies="korlana">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="56">A. euphorbiae korlana</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Draudt, M." box="[262,425,1056,1082]" pageId="8" pageNumber="56" refId="ref10251" refString="Draudt, M. (1931) In Seitz (ed). Die Gross-Schmetterlinge der Erde. Volume 3. Supplement. Alfred Kerner. 333 pp., 26 pl." type="book" year="1931">Draudt, 1931</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
from northwest 
<collectingCountry box="[639,711,1056,1082]" name="China" pageId="8" pageNumber="56">China</collectingCountry>
(
<collectingRegion box="[728,841,1056,1082]" country="China" name="Xinjiang Uygur" pageId="8" pageNumber="56">Xinjiang</collectingRegion>
). This record, however, apparently belongs to 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Hufnagel" baseAuthorityYear="1766" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Acronicta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="56" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cinerea">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="56">A. cinerea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. According to 
<bibRefCitation author="Fibiger, M. &amp; Ronkay L. &amp; A. Steiner &amp; A. Zilli" box="[413,641,1093,1119]" pageId="8" pageNumber="56" refId="ref10451" refString="Fibiger, M., Ronkay L., A. Steiner &amp; A. Zilli. (2009) Pantheinae, Dilobinae, Acronicitinae, Nolinae, Eustrotiinae, Acontiinae, Metoponiinae, Heliothinae and Bryophilinae. Noctuidae Europaea, 11. Entomological press, Soro, 504 pp." type="book" year="2009">
Fibiger 
<emphasis box="[505,556,1093,1118]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="56">et al</emphasis>
(2009)
</bibRefCitation>
<taxonomicName authorityName="Davis &amp; Schiffermuller" authorityYear="1775" box="[648,817,1093,1119]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Acronicta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="56" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="euphorbiae">
A. 
<emphasis box="[684,817,1093,1118]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="56">euphorbiae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has an Atlantic-Mediterranean distribution, while 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Hufnagel" baseAuthorityYear="1766" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Acronicta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="56" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cinerea">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="56">A. cinerea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is Euro-Asiatic. Our studyies (
<bibRefCitation author="Kononenko, V. S." box="[620,834,1130,1156]" pageId="8" pageNumber="56" refId="ref10544" refString="Kononenko, V. S. (2005) An annotated check list of the Noctuidae (s. l.) (Lepidoptera, Noctuoidea: Nolidae, Erebidae, Micronoctuidae, Noctuidae) of the Asian part of Russia and the Ural region. Noctuidae Sibiricae 1. Entomological Press, Soro, 243 pp." type="book" year="2005">Kononenko 2005</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Kononenko, V. S." box="[848,910,1130,1156]" pageId="8" pageNumber="56" refId="ref10602" refString="Kononenko, V. S. (2010) Micronoctuidae, Noctuidae: Rivulinae - Agaristinae (Lepidoptera). - Noctuidae Sibiricae 2. Entomological Press, Soro, 475 pp." type="book" year="2010">2010</bibRefCitation>
) indicate that only 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Hufnagel" baseAuthorityYear="1766" box="[1147,1270,1131,1156]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Acronicta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="56" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cinerea">
<emphasis box="[1147,1270,1131,1156]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="56">A. cinerea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
occurs in the Asian part of 
<collectingCountry box="[317,399,1168,1194]" name="Russia" pageId="8" pageNumber="56">Russia</collectingCountry>
, near 
<collectingCountry box="[472,547,1168,1194]" name="China" pageId="8" pageNumber="56">China</collectingCountry>
. Consequently, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Draudt" authorityYear="1931" box="[738,865,1168,1193]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Acronicta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="56" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="korlana">
<emphasis box="[738,865,1168,1193]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="56">A. korlana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
should be treated as a synonym of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Hufnagel" baseAuthorityYear="1766" box="[1293,1381,1168,1193]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Acronicta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="56" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cinerea">
<emphasis box="[1293,1381,1168,1193]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="56">cinerea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, not 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Davis &amp; Schiffermuller" authorityYear="1775" box="[151,284,1205,1230]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Acronicta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="56" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="euphorbiae">
<emphasis box="[151,284,1205,1230]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="56">euphorbiae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
